latestPosts.caption: POV : phone rakhne ka style kuj casual tha 🤣🤣🤣🤣

I’m not posting this to show off. I’m sharing this because the world needs more reminders of goodness.
We see enough of parties, alcohol, fake lifestyles on social media…
Let’s normalize helping. Let’s glorify kindness.

Doing this… fills my heart in a way I can’t explain.
The smile I saw today, the relief in their eyes — it gave me more happiness than anything money can ever buy.

A stomach that has stayed in hunger knows what it truly means to be hungry.
I feel proud and so blessed that God has made me capable of giving.
I pray I can continue to do this — more often, for more people.

May this not be just a one-time act… may it become a way of life.
#FromTheHeart #Gratitude #KindnessMatters #ProudToGive #CompassionOverClout
#normalizekindness

latestPosts.caption:
A rare sight in Hanoi today: Spotted what appeared to be French President Emmanuel Macron’s convoy passing by with intense security. While there was no official confirmation, the buzz on the street and the level of protection strongly pointed toward his presence.

President Macron is currently visiting Vietnam to strengthen France-Vietnam diplomatic and economic relations — a significant moment in international cooperation.

Amidst his visit, there’s also an ongoing controversy involving his wife, Brigitte Macron. But honestly, it’s unfair how certain media outlets sensationalize and speculate about personal matters. At the end of the day, even world leaders are human, and they deserve the space to live their personal lives without it being dissected under a global spotlight.

Witnessing this moment in Hanoi was so cool in itself.

#Hanoi #EmmanuelMacron #BrigitteMacron #FranceVietnam #Diplomacy #RespectPrivacy #GlobalPolitics #LeadershipInFocus #VietnamVibes
